Class GFGRandomGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • GFGRandomGraph
  • public class GFGRandomGraph
extends java.lang.Object
    GFGRandomGraph is a class for generating a random graph and writing it to a file for testing purposes. The graph is represented as an adjacency list and can have a random number of vertices and edges with a limit set for the maximum number of vertices and edge cost. It creates the a connected graph in the experiment to ensure no sparse graphs are in the experiment

        public void main()

The first line of the text file has the number of Vertices, Edges and Theoretical time complexity of Dijkstra's algorithm of the subgraph
